correctness.rationale: Several key values are correct and traceable (SALD method; TMA/O3; N2 as carrier/purging; 200 °C; ~760 Torr; GPC 1.33 Å/cycle; RI 1.63; amorphous; Al:O=1:1.53; film density 2.79 g/cm3; IGZO TFT μFE and VTH), but the extraction contains multiple schema violations, nulls in required numeric fields, and unit/type errors. Specific issues: (1) Schema/type violations: processParameters.plasmaPower is null (should be omitted or a valid object); processParameters.supercycleDesign is null (omit if not applicable); many required numeric fields set to null: thicknessControl.numberofCycles, thicknessControl.filmThickness, nucleationPeriod, dosingTime[*].precursor/coReactant, purgeTime[*].precursor/coReactant, flowRates[*].precursorFlow/coReactantFlow, materialProperties.uniformity.variation, conformality.aspectRatio, filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values, roughness.value; duplicate filmThickness with conflicting values (null inside thicknessControl vs 50 nm at processParameters level). (2) Unit noncompliance with schema: pressure.unit.sameAs uses Torr but schema allows only https://qudt.org/vocab/unit/MilliM_HG; filmDensity.unit.sameAs uses GM-PER-CM3 but schema allows GM-PER-DeciM3. (3) Factual/unit errors: subthresholdSwing reported as 0.14 mV, while the article’s 0.14 is in V/dec; if schema requires mV, it should be 140 mV; flow rate for separation/purging gas recorded as 4 with unit SCM-PER-MIN, while the article reports 4 slm (unit mismatch and magnitude inconsistency). (4) Minor: crystallinity characterizationMethod set to XRR (no explicit XRD; method should be reviewed). To improve: remove null properties or populate with article-backed numeric values; fix units to match schema (pressure in MilliM_HG; density in GM-PER-DeciM3) and correct SS to 140 mV (or 0.14 V if unit allowed); align flow-rate units with the reported slm or map consistently within schema constraints; resolve duplicate filmThickness and provide non-null values for all required fields.

completeness.rationale: Significant incompleteness and multiple schema violations. (1) Missing processes: the article describes a distinct PE-ALD IGZO deposition (DADI/TMGa/DEZ with O2 plasma at 200 °C, 10 nm, In:Ga:Zn=0.59:0.12:0.29) in addition to AP S-ALD Al2O3. Only the Al2O3 process was extracted. Each should be a separate process object. (2) Required fields present but null/invalid: thicknessControl.numberofCycles, thicknessControl.filmThickness (within thicknessControl), nucleationPeriod, dosingTime (precursor/co-reactant), purgeTime (precursor/co-reactant), flowRates.precursorFlow and coReactantFlow, materialProperties.uniformity.variation, conformality.aspectRatio, filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values, roughness.value, electricalProperties (resistivity, carrierDensity, mobility), deviceProperties.onOffRatio, otherAspects.safety/reproducibility. The schema does not allow nulls for these numeric/object fields. (3) Unit/schema mismatches: processParameters.pressure uses unit Torr but schema restricts to MilliM_HG; filmDensity unit GM-PER-CM3 but schema restricts GM-PER-DeciM3; flowRates uses 4 slm mapped to SCM-PER-MIN (sccm) without conversion; device subthresholdSwing entered as 0.14 mV while the article reports 0.14 V/dec (should be 140 mV if using the schema’s mV unit). (4) Optional objects incorrectly set to null instead of being omitted: plasmaPower, supercycleDesign, opticalProperties.absorptionCoefficient/bandGap, deviceProperties.onOffRatio, otherAspects.safety/reproducibility. (5) Missing but available from the article: precursor/reactant N2 flows used in saturation study (TMA zone total 50 sccm; O3 zone total 100 sccm), separation gas flow 4 slm (should be converted if reported as sccm), substrate speed 50 mm/s, Al:O atomic ratio (provided correctly) and elemental concentrations at 200 °C (Al 39.47 at%, O 60.53 at%), device stability/bias stress context. To improve completeness: add the IGZO PE-ALD process as a second process; remove null fields or populate with reported values; correct units to match schema (pressure to MilliM_HG; density to GM-PER-DeciM3 or adjust value/unit accordingly; convert 0.14 V/dec to 140 mV); fill flowRates with reported values; provide elemental concentrations; omit supercycleDesign and plasmaPower if not applicable.
